<br>
  Just a quick warning about MQ'ing.<br>
<br>
  Verant does NOT support MQ'ing. It isn't against the 'formal'<br>
  rules but if you lose your items you're stuck. I lost SoV legs<br>
  MQ'ing them and when we petitioned, the GM basically told<br>
  us we were SOL because Verant frowns on MQ'ing and that<br>
  GMs were, under no circumstances, to return items lost in<br>
  MQ'ing.<br>
<br>
  Manolas Autumnleaf<br>
  Druid of 59 seasons, Cazic Thule<br>
  Officer of Second Age <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualuien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aluien</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 3:01:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://bestanimations.com/Animals/Mammals/Dogs/Wolves/Wolf-02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> I hate to say it, but that GM is full of it. Verant likes Multiquesting as it's more of an oporatunity to get people to group. I Remember a thread on the wineplay boards a while back where Verant had a solution for Mobs eating your items when you handed in the wrong items for quests. Thier solution would have abolished Multiquesting all together so they decided not to implement it as they liked the idea of multiquesting and therefor would not tamper with it. The GMs simply won't help with quests unless it's a verified bug. Sorta makes you wanna be careful =).  <br>
<br>
 <p>Aluien Shadowstorm<BR>
57 Druid<BR>
CLAW<BR>
Master Fletcher (190)<BR>
Master Brewer (185)<BR>
Freedom is something you assume. Then you wait for someone to try to take it away from you. The degree to which you resist is the degree to which you are free.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 3:49:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> <A link=http://everquest.station.sony.com/support/policies/reimbursement_policy.jsp>http://everquest.station.sony.com/support/policies/reimbursement_policy.jsp</A><br>
<br>
13. Quests<br>
   13.1. Items lost in any Quest will not be reimbursed, regardless of the circumstance.<br>
   <b>13.2. Items that are lost/reward given to wrong person due to Multi-Questing will not be transferred or reimbursed.</b><br>
   13.3. NPC's in Quests that disappear or are killed will not be respawned, nor will items on the NPC's be reimbursed.<br>
   13.4. Items lost in any Quest performed incorrectly will not be reimbursed.<br>
<br>
 <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Preserver of the 55th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A> at: 6/18/01 3:53:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualuien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aluien</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 7:59:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://bestanimations.com/Animals/Mammals/Dogs/Wolves/Wolf-02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> Aye. All that states is that they will not reimburse you for giving to the wrong person. If the items are lost due to you handing in the correct items to the correct person with the properfaction etc... they wil reimburse you. Happened to a cleric friend of mine. He handed in his items to an NPC (not really familiar with the coeric epic) and the  NPC didn't say a word, No items, faction, not even a thank you. Lead GM reimbursed the items saying they found and validated the bug. <br>
<br>
But Verant likes multiquesting, that's why they didn't implement the change that would have made NPCs give back items if they were not correct. That would have done away with multiquesting all together.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
