</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/20/01 8:39:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.freshpope.com/gfx/ctree2sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> Don't try to do fancy things when multi-questing.  Just have one person hand the stuff in and say so when he's done.  Then the second person hands in stuff to get the reward.  You don't need to try to hand it in with both trade screens open at the same time or something like that.<br>
 <p>~Tunare's Enforcer~<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4080">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4050">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
Aerul Cuinnsear, 43 Rogue<br>
Undaunted, Xegony<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umanolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/01 2:37:12 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://manolasautumnleaf.homestead.com/files/dancing_sheep.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> <br>
  Actually, Verant does NOT support MQing. The GM I dealt<br>
  with was the head GM for Cazic Thule server. She was<br>
  extremely nice but said flat out that they frown on MQing.<br>
  We chatted for about 20 minutes she basically said the<br>
  quests were designed for a person to do not persons. Now<br>
  I know how to MQ, I've helped out with more Jboots quests<br>
  than I care to count and that has never been a problem,<br>
  same with epics blah blah blah. This was one of the SoV<br>
  armour quests that I was trying to do. I'm not saying that<br>
  it would fail in every case, that time was my first and only<br>
  failure, but I'd be prepared to be SOL if something goes<br>
  awry because the GMs will not help you.<br>
<br>
  Manolas Autumnleaf<br>
  Hierophant, Cazic Thule<br>
  Officer of Second Age <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubetina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>betina</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/01 6:27:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~mhuang/eq/pics/betina-new.gif height=120 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warning</span><hr size=1> Yes, even though multi-questing is mentioned in the manual, VI won't reimburse/exchange items lost in a transaction of this type. <br>
<br>
A lot of the quests are now dependant on faction, and NPCs will eat your item if you aren't of appropriate standing with them. This is probably the cause of  a high percentage of multiquest related requests for reimbursements. Having an NPC who is not KOS is often not enough, and in certain quests, even indifferent is not enough. <br>
<br>
If you want to take the risk of multiquesting, do it, just remember that you'll get no sympathy from Verant.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4780.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4778.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=4747.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.threadControl?topicID=4747.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4747.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4747.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgroveboardpostingrulesandpolicy">Board Posting Rules And Policy<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidiceq